library.description: GATK, pronounced "Gee Ay Tee Kay" (not "Gat-Kay"), stands for GenomeAnalysisToolkit. It is a collection of command-line tools for analyzing high-throughput sequencing (HTS) data in formats such as SAM/BAM/CRAM and VCF, with a focus on variant discovery. The relevant file formats are defined in the hts-specs repository; see especially the SAM specification and the VCF specification.
